metadata.title: How to take bulk actions on orders? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: How to take bulk actions on orders? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsDeliveryHow to take bulk actions on orders?How to take bulk actions on orders?Learn how to accept, ship and deliver orders through bulk actionsNWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoYou can now change the order statuses to accept, ship, or deliver in bulk and save time. To do that, go to the Orders sections. Click on the Change order status dropdown. You can see three options - Pending to Accepted, Accepted to Shipped, Self-Shipped to Delivered. Pending to Accepted If you want to Accept all the pending orders, choose this option from the dropdown. Select the orders that you want to Accept and click on the Change status to Accepted button. Accepted to Shipped If you want to Ship all the accepted orders, choose this option from the dropdown. Choose Dukaan Delivery or Self-Ship as delivery method and continue to proceed. Self-Shipped to Delivered If you want to Deliver all the shipped orders, choose this option from the dropdown. Select the orders that you want to deliver and click on the Change status to Delivered button to complete the action. metadata.doc: How to use the theme builder code editor to customise my theme? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsThemesHow to use the theme builder code editor to customise my theme?How to use the theme builder code editor to customise my theme?Learn how to use the code editor to edit your store theme.Written by Jyotbir Lamba Updated over a week agoWith the theme builder (code editor), you can edit your theme layout by getting access to the raw code for it. How to access the Code editor?In order to access the code editor, head over to the Appearance section on your Dukaan dashboard and click on Themes. Now, click on Cutomize on for your particular theme. You will see the Code editor option. Click on it. This will open the code repository for that particular theme as you can see below. On the left side, you will see the repositories for the code files:Public - Access of the public data that you can edit using the theme editor. This includes data about your products, categories, customers, etc.You can make changes to your theme files as you may see fit. Once you have made the changes, you can click on the Preview button to view these changes and click on Publish to make them live on your site. metadata.doc: How to use Store QR Code? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsMobileHow to use Store QR Code?How to use Store QR Code?Learn how to download and use your Store QR Code on AppNWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoStore QR code helps customers to easily find your business and place orders without any hassle of typing links in the web browser. Now you can get your own store’s QR Code with a single click. To get the QR code, click on Manage and then select Store QR Code.  You’ll see the store QR code, which you can download or share directly with your customers by clicking on the Print PDF button. You can take the print of this QR code and put them up inside your store, which will help customers to place their orders and help them to skip the queue. Or, this can be printed on flyers, pamphlets and can be distributed offline for your store promotion. Click on Orders and select the order for which you want to download the receipt.   After clicking on the order, you’ll see the below screen. Click on the Share Receipt button at the bottom to share or download the order receipt.  You can also generate the report for all orders in one go. You can filter orders via their order status or day, week, month-wise, or lifetime (orders to date) as per your requirement. To generate the order report, click on Report at the bottom. It lets you create digital menus of your restaurant for each table. Customers can scan the QR code to browse the cuisines and place the order directly.  To generate the QR menu for each table, go to Manage and then select Restaurant Dining. Click on Add a table to get started. Enter the table name and click on Add table. Your restaurant table will be added. If you want to download the QR menu for the table, click on the table name. Then click on the three dots icon as highlighted in the image below and click on Download Table QR.  In case you no longer want orders from a table or want to delete the table, you can do this as well. To proceed, click on the three dots button of the desired table and select View table details. Once clicked, you’ll see the below screen. metadata.title: How to use the Shippo plugin? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: How to use the Shippo plugin? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsDeliveryHow to use the Shippo plugin?How to use the Shippo plugin?NWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoNote: This is only applicable to sellers outside of India. Shippo helps you ship your products across at the best prices. To start using the plugin, go to Plugins and install the Shippo plugin. Once you've installed the plugin, enter the Shippo Token and Warehouse Address details as shown below and save it.  Here's how you can start using Shippo on your Dukaan store:Create a Shippo account or login if you have oneUnder Integrations, click on APIClick on Generate Token under the Live Token sectionCopy this token and paste this hereRefer to this article to know more. To start shipping orders from Shippo, go to Orders and select any order that you want to ship. Now, accept the order and click on the Ship order button. You'll see here that you can ship orders via Shippo or ship them manually. To use Shippo, enter the weight of the shipment and select the courier partner from the options.   When you proceed to ship, you'll see the confirmation screen. Here, click on Pay and Request delivery to raise the pickup request. The amount will be deducted from your Shippo account.  Did this answer your question?😞😐😃Dukaan® for PCPrivacy PolicyAbout Dukaan®FacebookTwitterLinkedInIntercomWe run on Intercom
